Ukraine’s Government, Companies Agree to Cap Petroleum Prices

-- B y   D a r y n a   K r a s n o l u t s k a
-- 
2011-03-12T11:15:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-12/ukraine-s-government-companies-agree-to-cap-petroleum-prices.html
Ukraine’s government said it agreed
with oil companies to cap prices for petroleum on the domestic
market, the  Energy and Coal Industry Ministry  said.  The price will not exceed 9.5 hryvnia ($1.2) per liter
(0.26 gallon), while for diesel it was set at 9 hryvnia per
liter, the Kiev-based ministry said today in an e-mailed
statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Daryna Krasnolutska in Kiev at 
 dkrasnolutsk@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Willy Morris at   wmorris@bloomberg.net . 